Cape Town - A body was located in Mossel Bay by the National Sea Rescue Institute (NSRI) on Monday, and thereafter was recovered and taken into the care of Police and the Forensic Pathology Services.Â At 15:50 on the 21 January, NSRI Station 15 Mossel Bay duty crew were activated by the Transnet National Ports Authority (TNPA) following eye-witness reports of a body suspected to be floating in the water off-shore of Mossel Bay Point. The SA Police Services, the Police Dive Unit and Police Sea Borderline Control were activated and the NSRI sea rescue craft St Blaze Rescuer was launched. NSRI rescue crew were dispatched by land and confirmed a body was floating close in-shore. On arrival at the scene, NSRI crew aboard St Blaze Rescuer located and recovered a body of an unidentified female suspected to be a teenager and the body was brought to shore and the body has been taken into the care of the Forensic Pathology Services and Police. Police have opened an inquest docket. * Supplied by the NSRI. argusnews@inl.co.za Cape Argus